    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>AIR WINDSHIELD WIPERS (ROOF MOUNTED) WITH HEADER MOUNTED SWITCHES</title>
            <para>Wiper motors operate on air pressure supplied by the vehicle's compressed air system. Each wiper arm
                is powered by individual air motors that are located inside the cab behind the header panel. Each
                windshield wiper is controlled by its own operating valve. Wiper speeds are infinitely variable between
                HI and LOW.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
